thread.title: Governors Headed for Showdown Over Port Authority

author: Paul Berger
title: Governors Headed for Showdown Over Port Authority
text:
Just four months after taking office, New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy looks set to square off with his New York counterpart over control of a sprawling bistate agency.
The two Democratic governors share control of the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey, an agency with an annual budget of $8.1 billion which runs the regionâ€™s major airports, six bridges and tunnels as well as the 16-acre World Trade Center site.
